Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.74,0:00:09.69,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,The countless flowers,\Nenveloped in light...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.69,0:00:19.81,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,...gaze at tomorrow\Nwith unwavering eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:39.35,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Everyone wishes for me to be pure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:46.81,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,...but what can I bring\Nwith me to the frayed skies?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.81,0:00:53.90,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,What I've made my own\Nby breaking off flowers in bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:59.54,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,All such sinful things...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.54,0:01:07.01,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Why did I stop making\Npromises with the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.01,0:01:14.25,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Because even if I try\Nto run far from all the pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.25,0:01:20.99,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,...a cold wind rustles\Nmy hair... Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.99,0:01:28.08,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Where can I ever find the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.43,0:01:34.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am Anubituf,\Nthe captain of the Arcus Prima...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:39.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,...one of the largest airships\Nin Simulacrum Kyuukoku's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.78,0:01:44.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,Three air squadrons, Simoun chors,\Nare stationed on the Arcus Prima.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.68,0:01:50.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest,\NChor Caput, and Chor Rubor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.21,0:01:56.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,But Chor Tempest, once prided for\Ndefense and flawless Ri Majons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.34,0:02:01.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,...has lost its high standing and is now\Nbeing relegated to reserve status.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:06.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,And now, as we escort\Nthe Plumbum highland delegation...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:10.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,...to international waters, where\Na peace conference is scheduled...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.07,0:02:16.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,...tensions in Chor Tempest over its\Nnew members have sparked a brawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:24.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest has been ordered to\Ndisband as soon as we return to port.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.78,0:02:29.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,For those with reasons for wanting\Nto continue flying the Simouns...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:31.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,...it is a bitter sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.09,0:02:34.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Either way, when it's time\Nto journey to the Spring...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:37.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,...one can no longer fly a Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.03,0:02:41.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,And now the peace\Nconference is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.64,0:02:49.64,Titles,,70,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.44,0:02:54.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,We understand that your priestesses\Nare all fluent in Kyuukoku's language.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.65,0:02:59.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,But for translating purposes,\Nwouldn't just one suffice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:05.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,We are not mere interpreters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.32,0:03:08.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,We also watch over\Nthis important conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.49,0:03:10.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,And several are needed\Nfor certain ceremonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.73,0:03:13.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:18.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,We should have some of Tempus\NSpatium's priestesses attend as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:19.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.07,0:03:25.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,They are not merely priestesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.11,0:03:27.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but soldiers too, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:39.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,How long will you snivel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:42.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, we've been disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:44.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,We should be crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:49.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,But at least now we can\Nfinally stop flying Simouns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:57.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina, what have\Nyou been doing since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.64,0:04:02.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,You lived with your mother after\Nyour father passed away, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.12,0:04:04.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.75,0:04:09.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've got to keep flying Simouns.\NI have to remain a sibylla...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.22,0:04:14.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's just like Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:19.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,You want to go on\Nbeing a sibylla too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:21.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:24.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why? As long as you're a sibylla,\Nyou don't have to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.86,0:04:27.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.08,0:04:30.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,We all want to go to the Spring,\Nbut since becoming sibyllae...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.71,0:04:35.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,...we have to take part in this war now\Nand are unable to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.18,0:04:39.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's not like it's forbidden.\NJust quit being a sibylla, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:42.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,After being finally\Nchosen after such toil?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:47.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I do have my pride as a priestess.\NAvoiding the front line isn't an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:49.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,We all have our reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:53.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but I've never seen anyone who\Nwanted to avoid going to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:57.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh? If you want to see, be my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:04:58.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:01.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.10,0:05:04.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:08.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,This ballroom is where Chor Tempest\Nsocializes. It's always been that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.12,0:05:12.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,People like the captain\Nnever decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:15.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,But it's always been\Nthat way, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.76,0:05:18.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,You guys never used to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:22.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're on standby and might\Nscramble at any time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.50,0:05:23.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:39.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, jeez, I can't stand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:43.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big Sister, why don't\Nyou come to my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:47.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, everybody! Big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.53,0:05:50.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big news! Big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.49,0:05:54.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,She always seems to be having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.49,0:05:58.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's been decided that just two\Nof the highland priestesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.73,0:06:02.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,...will be allowed\Nto attend the peace conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:07.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Meaning that this priestess here,\NAnglas, will not be allowed to attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:11.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,She'll stay with Chor Tempest\Nuntil the conference is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:14.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because we're fellow priestesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:18.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,We can leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.38,0:06:22.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'll be patrolling the conference site.\NI hope everything's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.48,0:06:23.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't offend our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:32.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,The only thing is we don't\Nspeak the same language...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:37.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am not fluent, but I can speak a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:46.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've heard many highland priestesses\Nare from the border near Kyuukoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.44,0:06:51.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right, speaking of which, that area's\Ntribes travel between the countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.62,0:06:57.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,They say our god was once\Nthe same deity that you worship here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:00.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's why, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.85,0:07:02.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,You feel an affinity with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,The little one is Rimone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.20,0:07:14.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,The two on the right are Alty and Kaim.\NThey're sisters, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:15.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:20.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rimone, Alty, Kaim, Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.14,0:07:22.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,And there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:26.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Starting from the right, Paraietta,\NDominüra, and Roatreamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta, Dominüra, Roatreamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:32.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,What a lovely name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:36.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's a very noble name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:41.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,From a venerable family that's borne\Ngenerations of Simoun sibyllae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.80,0:07:45.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,And the girl who just spoke up\Nis Mamina. Next to her is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:46.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm Yun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:51.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I wish for\Na speedy end to the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:55.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to know there will soon\Nbe peace between our countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.71,0:07:57.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina and Yun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.45,0:08:01.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's what I wish for too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.12,0:08:02.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,My name's Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.92,0:08:03.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:06.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let's see... Who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:08.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,The girl in the very back is Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.99,0:08:13.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,The only one missing is Neviril.\NAnd that's everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.43,0:08:18.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.27,0:08:22.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Now that introductions are done...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:23.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:32.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're the only one\Nshe didn't call by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.56,0:08:35.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she said\Neveryone's name but mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.93,0:08:38.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Does she have\Nto say every single name?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:40.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,How tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:42.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,I know it is, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:44.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Say, what do you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.99,0:08:47.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,We're priestesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.70,0:08:51.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,But we turned the Simouns\Ninto weapons of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:52.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,To do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:56.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,In the eyes of normal priestesses\Nlike you, it's peculiar, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.89,0:09:03.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is very cold in the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.88,0:09:08.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,We're blessed by\Na compassionate god, but even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:10.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Every year, there is a cold snap,\Nresulting in many deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.15,0:09:14.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am a priestess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.90,0:09:20.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,...so I pray that those who have\Nperished may find bliss in God's arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:26.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,When we first started as sibyllae...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:31.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I thought we would fly Simouns\Nin divine ceremonies like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.46,0:09:36.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're right. We should be flying\Nthe Simouns in order to pray...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:38.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,What a carefree attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:44.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,You take becoming a sibylla\Nfor granted, so you can say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:46.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that, Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:54.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for this war,\NI never could have become a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:02.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,There were only a handful\Nof young girls in my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:08.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't hard to serve the great\Ntemple as a priestess in training.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.04,0:10:09.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:16.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:21.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,When I become a sibylla,\Nwill you fly with me as my pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.46,0:10:24.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,You? A sibylla?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.23,0:10:29.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibyllae are selected by Tempus\NSpatium. People of humble birth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:35.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,And then that day came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:39.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,Plumbum highland's death squad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.98,0:10:43.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,...crossed the border and\Ntook up position in our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:49.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Their goal was of course to steal\Nthe Simouns from the great temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.06,0:10:52.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,There was no time to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:55.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,We had to launch the Simouns\Nand repulse them from the skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:11:01.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,The sibyllae said, "We are\Npriestesses. We can't go into battle."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:05.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,The dux turned to\Nthe trainees for volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.23,0:11:11.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:15.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tempus Spatium will never allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:18.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,One such as you\Ncould never fly a Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:56.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,And so I became a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:12:00.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,But only because I was\Naccomplished in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:04.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, being of low birth\Nand having no connections...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:06.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I would've been stripped\Nof my post right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:12.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,If only I could pair up\Nwith Neviril... With Sibylla Aurea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.00,0:12:15.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then no one could ever\Ntreat me like an upstart again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.88,0:12:18.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I could prove there's\Nno better sibylla in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.35,0:12:22.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.48,0:12:25.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.12,0:12:26.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:30.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's not something one\Nshould tell another land's priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.93,0:12:32.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:36.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,But anyway, I'm sure keeping\Nme company is very dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.13,0:12:38.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please go about your day freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:43.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh? You can take a tour of the ship\Nas long as it's not a restricted area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.40,0:12:45.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'd like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:48.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then as my guide... Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.17,0:12:53.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's Aer, all right? Call me by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.55,0:13:43.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is it all right to go into\Nanother god's chapel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:47.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned earlier,\Nthe recent theory is that our god...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.14,0:13:53.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,...was once the same as your\Nown deity, Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.07,0:13:58.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then does that mean your country\Nused to be a colony of ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:13:59.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.75,0:14:02.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Before Tempus Spatium...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:06.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,...there may have been\Nan even more ancient religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:14.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.33,0:14:15.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm not a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:24.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, forget her. She's just here since\Nshe doesn't want to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.07,0:14:25.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Praying to gods is trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:30.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? You haven't\Npicked a gender yet either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:32.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, no, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.64,0:14:41.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you're not sure, forcing an answer\Nwould be even more ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.20,0:14:59.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,A Plumbum dictionary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.29,0:15:00.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:03.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's the problem?\NYou and I are a pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:04.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:21.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'll check on the conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.26,0:15:24.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:27.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:41.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Those fireworks were a signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.98,0:15:43.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,First, where's the priestess?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:45.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer-sama, Sibylla Aurea is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:07.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's got my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:08.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why would she...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:15.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.19,0:16:18.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's as it seems.\NThis is how they do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:21.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,The conference was\Na diversion for their infiltration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:22.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,To take a Simoun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.03,0:16:25.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,You can't fly that Simoun, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.22,0:16:30.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's a priestess, right? If there\Nwere two, it might be possible to fly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:35.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,If she does, what are those people\Nin the conference planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.17,0:16:39.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Waporif, block the maintenance\Nhangar off from the conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:41.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't let two highland\Npriestesses rendezvous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:44.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear her? Move it!\NWe're blocking all access!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.51,0:16:50.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Do you really think\Nyou're going to pull this off?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:51.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.62,0:16:59.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:01.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Alty! Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.40,0:17:04.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Grab her!\NDon't let her touch that Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.71,0:17:19.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:21.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:34.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you're unsure of yourself,\Nyou'll never find an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.12,0:17:36.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,Run, Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:37.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.83,0:17:39.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right. Bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:39.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Run, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.23,0:17:42.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's got bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.23,0:17:48.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.93,0:18:20.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.27,0:18:28.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:42.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Nearly all the Simouns\Nhere were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.26,0:18:44.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have to see\Nif the ones spared work...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.67,0:18:46.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Which can fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.03,0:18:47.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Only the Simouns on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:52.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Only Chor Tempest's\NSimouns, you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.44,0:18:58.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Aer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.25,0:19:02.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,That girl called out "Aer"...\NAt the very end...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.08,0:19:03.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:06.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,But why? Why my name...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:09.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because it's not\Na person's name to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:13.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,The word "aer" in her own language...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:16.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,...means "the highest love of all."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.09,0:19:22.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,"Aer" means "the love of god"\Nin the Plumbum language.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:28.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.87,0:19:33.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just what is it about this "love of god"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.64,0:19:38.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can it make\Nsomeone do a thing like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:24.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea,\Nplease fly with me as your pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:28.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just heard that Chor Tempest's\NSimouns are the only ones intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.28,0:20:31.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're completely sure\Nabout this, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.29,0:20:33.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,We don't have time not to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:36.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer, what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:42.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:45.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:55.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer, you came here\Nto fly a Simoun, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.16,0:20:59.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just don't want to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:04.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,But is that a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.73,0:21:09.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't even have\Nlove of god or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:14.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,You needn't come up with an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.62,0:21:30.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm unsure too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:33.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,About being a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.14,0:21:34.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,About going into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:38.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Whether those are\Nthe right things to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.51,0:21:43.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,You and I are completely\Ndifferent in every respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:47.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,But we're alike in just one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.51,0:21:50.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Stand up, Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.84,0:21:52.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am your pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.19,0:22:10.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,One second is enough. Right the ship.\NWe're launching the Simouns.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.04,0:22:12.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rubor and Caput were destroyed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.93,0:22:15.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest will be going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.16,0:22:47.87,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,It is played by my wounds...\Nthe song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.87,0:22:52.11,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Let it ring out over\Nthe grieving universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.11,0:22:59.15,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Can we change tomorrow?\NDon't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.15,0:23:06.92,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I want to let you know\Nhow my heart's overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.60,0:23:19.67,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,"I want to get closer to you."\N"I want to feel your pulse."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.67,0:23:24.84,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I was too defiant,\Nand I took the long way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:28.85,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,The blue moon is swaying silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.85,0:23:32.86,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,My true heart's desire is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.86,0:23:38.73,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I can't reach you.\NMy tears of pain trickle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:44.27,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Soar away into the sky, song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.27,0:23:47.70,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Carrying my love that came too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.70,0:23:53.37,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,What can I do to change tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.37,0:23:59.77,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Just hold on to "now" the way it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.59,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.28,0:24:08.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,We will soon be performing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.46,0:24:13.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,...our last Ri Majon as members of\NChor Tempest at the great temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.42,0:24:16.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time on Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.62,0:24:19.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.43,0:24:19.93,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}The Hearing
